milestones.description: Khurram Khan and Shahzad's 160-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 94 between Mazhar Hussain and Vijay Mehra
Saqib Ali and Khurram Khan's 76-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 50 between Rohan Mustafa and Swapnil Patil
Guruge has conceded the most runs in an innings (81) in ODIs for UAE, going past Khurram Khan's record of 78
Nawroz Mangal's 129 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AFG), surpassing Shahzad's 118
Khurram Khan's 132 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for UAE), surpassing Swapnil Patil's 99
Khurram Khan has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (74) in an innings in ODIs for UAE, going past Saleem Raza's 64
This is the highest match aggregate (562) involving teams U.A.E. & Afghanistan in ODIs
Khurram Khan and Shahzad's 160-run partnership is UAE's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 117 between Saleem Raza and Azhar Saeed
Khurram Khan has broken the record for most catches (5) in ODIs for UAE, going past Tauqir's 4
Samiullah Shinwari has scored 7 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AFG breaking Mohammad Nabi's record
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 3
Mohammad Nabi has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (39) for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari

stories.title: Shahzad, Farooq reported for suspect actions
stories.subTitle: UAE news
stories.seoTitle: Shahzad, Salman Farooq reported for suspect actions
stories.summary: UAE medium-pacer Mohammad Shahzad and offspinner Salman Farooq have been reported for suspect illegal bowling actions by the ICC after the second ODI against Afghanistan on November 30 in Dubai

stories.title: Khurram's record 132* powers UAE win
stories.subTitle: UAE v Afghanistan, 2nd ODI, Dubai
stories.summary: At 43 years and 162 days, UAE captain Khurram Khan became the oldest player to score an ODI hundred, his unbeaten 132 helping the team to a six-wicket victory against Afghanistan in Dubai
